summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 23892, entitled "An Ordinance authorizing the Mayor and City Comptroller to issue Local Improvement bonds for the improvement of Thirty-third Avenue North from East Madison Street to East Mercer Street, et al., in the City of Seattle, by grading, etc. under Ordinance No. 19844, creating Local Improvement District No. 1926, prescribing the rate of interest thereon and authorizing their delivery to the contractor constructing the improvement," approved April 18, 1910.
